<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idec0e1550-3a70-11f1-9081-fe88c1712d53" identifier="/us/usc/t51/s70703"><num value="70703">§ 70703.</num><heading> Tasks of Commission</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">A Commission established pursuant to this chapter shall, to the extent possible, undertake the following tasks:</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idec0e1551-3a70-11f1-9081-fe88c1712d53" identifier="/us/usc/t51/s70703/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><heading> <inline class="small-caps">Investigation</inline>.—</heading><content>Investigate the incident.</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idec0e1552-3a70-11f1-9081-fe88c1712d53" identifier="/us/usc/t51/s70703/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><heading> <inline class="small-caps">Cause</inline>.—</heading><content>Determine the cause of the incident.</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idec0e1553-3a70-11f1-9081-fe88c1712d53" identifier="/us/usc/t51/s70703/3"><num value="3">(3)</num><heading> <inline class="small-caps">Contributing factors</inline>.—</heading><content>Identify all contributing factors to the cause of the incident.</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idec0e1554-3a70-11f1-9081-fe88c1712d53" identifier="/us/usc/t51/s70703/4"><num value="4">(4)</num><heading> <inline class="small-caps">Recommendations</inline>.—</heading><content>Make recommendations for corrective actions.</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idec0e1555-3a70-11f1-9081-fe88c1712d53" identifier="/us/usc/t51/s70703/5"><num value="5">(5)</num><heading> <inline class="small-caps">Additional findings or recommendations</inline>.—</heading><content>Provide any additional findings or recommendations deemed by the Commission to be important, whether or not they are related to the specific incident under investigation.</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idec0e1556-3a70-11f1-9081-fe88c1712d53" identifier="/us/usc/t51/s70703/6"><num value="6">(6)</num><heading> <inline class="small-caps">Report</inline>.—</heading><content>Prepare a report to Congress, the President, and the public.</content>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="idec0e1557-3a70-11f1-9081-fe88c1712d53">(<ref href="/us/pl/111/314/s3">Pub. L. 111–314, § 3</ref>, <date date="2010-12-18">Dec. 18, 2010</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/124/3432">124 Stat. 3432</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
